<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/41842470-bookwormlife"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1504608810i/41842470._UX100_CR0,0,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/41842470-bookwormlife">BookwormLife</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<div class='spoiler'>
This answer contains spoilers…
<span class='spoilerAnswerText'>
<a class="jsShowSpoiler spoilerAction">(view spoiler)</a><span class="spoilerContainer" style="display: none">[
  
    I could have seen an epilogue,but at the same time, i don’t think it would have said anything positive necessarily. All of the characters, Joanna,rob,<a href="#" rel="nofollow noopener">…more</a>
    I could have seen an epilogue,but at the same time, i don’t think it would have said anything positive necessarily. All of the characters, Joanna,rob,Kira and Spence even Jason, no one had a happy ending. I feel like the ending suited the book, what was done was done and in a way of freed Kira and Joanna and i think that’s what the author wanted. <a href="#" rel="nofollow noopener">(less)</a>
  
 <a class="jsHideSpoiler spoilerAction">(hide spoiler)</a>]</span>
</span>
</div>
</span>
